Private Sub Report_Open(Cancel As Integer)

  On Error GoTo SubError

  Dim Instrg As String
  Dim instrg2 As String

  boldon = "ZZX"
  boldoff = "ZZZ"

  Me.Filter = "TO_STATE = 'Y' OR TO_STATE = 'A'"
  MsgBox "This report creates a text file of State Winners grouped by: " & vbCrLf & _
         " 1.) T0_State / Alternates (Alternates at end of report)" & vbCrLf & _
         " 2.) School, 3.) Students (sorted by last name)" & vbCrLf & _

         "3. Fields (*Groups) used for Report Sort order:" & vbCrLf & _
         "  * 1st  [TO_STATE]  ('Y' or 'A') " & vbcrfl & _
         "  * 2nd= [SCHOOL]  (School of student or teacher winner)" & vbCrLf & _

        "  example: to 'exclude' grade 7 enter:" & vbCrLf & _
        "    GRADE <> 7 " & vbCrLf & _
        "  example: to 'include' only Albuquerque schools enter:" & vbCrLf & _
        "    SchCty = 'Albuquerque'" & vbCrLf & _
        " (leave this blank if no additional criteria)"
TryAgain:
  Instrg = InputBox(msg, "Filter Criteria")
  If Len(Instrg) > 0 Then
    Me.Filter = Me.Filter & " AND " & Instrg
  End If
  Me.FilterOn = True
  ' ------------------------  the Text file to be created ------------------
  msg = "Note: Current folder/directory is " & CurDir & "\ " & vbCrLf & _
        "      Output file will be in the current folder" & vbCrLf & _
        "      unless you enter a complete path name." & vbCrLf & _
        "ENTER A UNIQUE FILE NAME." & vbCrLf & _
        "  i.e. 'JnlToState.txt' or 'C:/SF_Access/Data/MtNewsTS.txt'"

  msg = "Enter the Newspaper Name" & vbCrLf & _
        " (will be included in the text file header)"
  Instrg = InputBox(msg, "Newspaper", "Albuquerque Journal")
  PaperNam = Instrg
  msg = "Enter the name of the person to receive the data" & vbCrLf & _
        " (will be included in the text file header)"
  instrg2 = InputBox(msg, "Recipient", "John Fleck")

           Format(Date, "MMM DD, YYYY") & " " & Format(Now, "hh:mm AMPM")

  Print #1, "sorted by 1.) School name, 2.) Winner name."
  Print #1, "'" & boldon & "' Starts text to be printed bold,  '" & boldoff & "' Stops bold text."
  Print #1, "Thank you for your support of the Regional Research Challenge."
  Print #1, ""
  Exit Sub
SubError:
  MsgBox Err.Description
End Sub

   On Error GoTo SubError
    Me.tbHeader = "State Winners/Alts to: " & PaperNam & " " & PersonNam & Format(Date, "mmm dd, yyyy") & _
                  " " & Format(Now, "hh:mm AMPM")
    ' see if user enter the full path

      tbRptInfo = " Output File is: " & Filenam
    Else ' seems user just entered a file name

    End If
   Exit Sub
SubError:
   MsgBox Err.Description
End Sub
Private Sub GroupHeader1_Print(Cancel As Integer, PrintCount As Integer)
  '  Comes here on change of TO_STATE.
  On Error GoTo SubError
starthere:
  If OKtoStart Then
    Print #1, ""  '   do crlf
    Print #1, ""  '   do crlf
    Print #1, "----------" & Me.tbToState & "--------"   ' with crlf after
  Else
    If GotFirst Then
      If Me.tbToState = FirstGrp Then
        OKtoStart = True
        GoTo starthere
      End If
    Else
      FirstGrp = Me.tbToState
      GotFirst = True
    End If
  End If
  Exit Sub
SubError:
  MsgBox Err.Description
End Sub
Private Sub GroupHeader0_Print(Cancel As Integer, PrintCount As Integer)
  On Error GoTo SubError
  '  come here each time format a new School
  If OKtoStart Then
    If TestPrint Then
      Print #1, Me.SCHOOL
    Else
      NewSch = True
      Print #1, ""    ' do crlf at first or after last list
      Print #1, boldon & Me.SCHOOL & ": " & boldoff;   ' no crlf - let next section do it
    End If
  End If
  Exit Sub
SubError:
  MsgBox Err.Description
End Sub

Private Sub Detail_Print(Cancel As Integer, PrintCount As Integer)
  ' come here each time format a new student/prize '
  On Error GoTo SubError
  If OKtoStart Then
    If TestPrint Then
      Print #1, "  " & Me.studname   '  Do crlf for test
    Else
      If NewSch = True Then '  have a new school so this is first student
        NewSch = False
      Else
        Print #1, ", ";  '
      End If
      Print #1, Me.studname;   '  Do not do crlf
    End If
  End If
  Exit Sub
SubError:
  MsgBox Err.Description
End Sub
Private Sub Report_Close()
  On Error GoTo ErrorSub
  Close #1
  Exit Sub
ErrorSub:
  MsgBox Err.Description
End Sub
